WEBVTT

00:01.560 --> 00:06.190
I never get used to its magnitude, what
it's taken to keep this country free.

00:06.280 --> 00:11.832
All societies build monuments to their dead
to convince combatants it's an honour to die.

00:11.920 --> 00:13.717
For these servicemen, it was.

00:13.800 --> 00:18.635
And for somebody to use this place
to protest the warjust pisses me off.

00:18.720 --> 00:21.678
These lives gave them that
right. They should be respected.

00:21.760 --> 00:24.558
If they were respected,
fewer'd be buried here.

00:24.640 --> 00:27.029
- We gonna get into something?
- I don't see why.

00:27.120 --> 00:30.556
We both wish this place
were a lot smaller.

00:30.640 --> 00:34.269
Agent Booth, Dr Brennan, right this way.

00:34.920 --> 00:41.712
Must've happened in the middle of the night.
The place is so big no one saw the fire.

00:43.720 --> 00:47.918
- The accelerant was charcoaI starter.
- We didn't find a suicide note.

00:48.000 --> 00:52.994
- A protester would leave a note.
- Didn't need to. It's on Charlie Kent's grave.

00:53.080 --> 00:57.437
Press was coming today to do a tribute
to him. One-year anniversary of his death.

00:57.520 --> 00:59.988
- Charlie Kent?
- In the NationaI Guard.

01:00.080 --> 01:03.152
About to be drafted by the NBA
when he got shipped out to Iraq.

01:03.240 --> 01:08.951
He gave his life killing a group of insurgents
to save his unit. Won the Silver Star.

01:09.040 --> 01:11.952
It's male, African descent,

01:12.040 --> 01:17.512
approximately 20 to 29 years old.
Too early to determine cause of death.

01:17.600 --> 01:22.435
- I'm not a pro, but I'm guessing fire.
- The White House and DOD want an ID ASAP.

01:22.520 --> 01:25.637
- So they can brand him a traitor.
- Why so cynicaI?

01:25.720 --> 01:28.757
I'm not. It's a necessary part
of the psychology of warfare.

01:28.840 --> 01:33.197
Heroes and villains. Without clear
distinctions, we'd never be able to fight.

01:33.280 --> 01:37.353
Well, I always found being
shot at is a motivating factor.

01:37.440 --> 01:43.993
Bag these fragments of his clothing. I also
want any singed plant life or debris you find.

01:44.080 --> 01:46.071
<i>I'm on it.</i>

01:51.720 --> 01:53.995
What?

01:54.080 --> 01:55.877
It's Jamie Richards.

01:55.960 --> 01:58.520
We were in the Rangers together.

01:58.600 --> 02:03.390
He was hit by a roadside bomb
just... outside the green zone.

02:04.680 --> 02:08.592
He left a... wife and two kids.

02:11.400 --> 02:17.475
- The fact that he was near this...
- You believe somehow he's here watching?

02:17.560 --> 02:20.154
Yeah. You don't. I get that.

02:21.760 --> 02:25.435
I know you think he's
a good man. That's...

02:25.520 --> 02:27.511
That's enough for me.

02:28.960 --> 02:33.238
Zack, I want pictures of all
remaining tissue before he's moved.

02:33.320 --> 02:37.996
<i>The unidentified suicide victim was
found at Private Kent's grave today.</i>

02:38.080 --> 02:42.949
<i>Services had been planned to honour Kent on
the one-year anniversary of his death in Iraq.</i>

02:43.040 --> 02:46.396
Ah, I used to love watching
Kent play. He could fly.

02:46.480 --> 02:49.597
He made 46.4% of his three-point
attempts in his last season.

02:49.680 --> 02:53.992
- A basketball fan? I'm surprised.
- Zack, I'd like you to keep cleaning the bones.

02:54.080 --> 02:57.914
<i>Did you see the game against North
Carolina? 53 points and 18 rebounds.</i>

02:58.000 --> 03:00.116
Zack!

03:00.200 --> 03:03.875
- Sorry. Cleaning.
- It's difficult knowing he'll never play again.

03:03.960 --> 03:08.238
- It makes the war so reaI.
- Which is odd, since fiction got us there.

03:08.320 --> 03:14.475
- Shouldn't we stand up to tyrants?
- I've waited for the press to do it for 3 years.

03:14.560 --> 03:17.597
- I can't believe you took the bait.
- Yeah. Me neither.

03:19.520 --> 03:24.230
Oh! Press Office of Defence. Please ID
him. This is the third call in an hour.

03:24.320 --> 03:30.190
Hello? Yes. It's a pleasure to hear from
you again, sir. Yes. We're very close.

03:30.280 --> 03:35.991
I fed his dentals, approximate age, height
and sketch I made from the tissue markers

03:36.080 --> 03:38.071
into the DOD database.

03:38.160 --> 03:42.790
The victim had lamb about an hour before
his death. Of course it's overcooked now.

03:42.880 --> 03:46.509
- Toasted himself. Who cares what he ate?
- Just doing ourjobs, Booth.

03:46.600 --> 03:50.195
- Been told to sweep this under the
rug? - Can the left-wing conspiracy.

03:50.280 --> 03:53.352
- Probably one of your nut-ball
friends. - Don't think so.

03:53.440 --> 03:57.513
Fabric at the scene was cotton with synthetic polymers
- dye, olive green.

03:57.600 --> 04:02.037
This dude was wearing a military
uniform. He's one of yours, not mine.

04:02.120 --> 04:05.635
<i>OK. His name is Devon Marshall.</i>

04:05.720 --> 04:09.315
- He served in the Guard with Kent.
- What?

04:09.400 --> 04:12.392
He was there in MosuI,
the night Kent was killed.

04:12.480 --> 04:16.995
- He was protesting?
- Marshall could've had a change of heart.

04:17.079 --> 04:21.197
Or it was survivor guilt. The guy
who saved his life didn't make it.

04:21.279 --> 04:23.555
You can't imagine what that's like.

04:23.640 --> 04:29.875
I don't think so. There's evidence of
damage on the auditory meatus. Here and here.

04:29.960 --> 04:32.394
I'm sorry, but I left
my phrase book at home.

04:32.480 --> 04:35.711
The opening where the auditory
nerves feed into the brain.

04:35.800 --> 04:37.916
- So we're talking ear hole?
- Yes!

04:38.000 --> 04:42.835
- They simplify these words for a reason.
- Something was jabbed into his ear.

04:42.920 --> 04:45.036
OK, that's clear. But why?

04:45.120 --> 04:50.069
There's scrapings in the cranium, and marks
on the inside of the parietaI and occipitaI.

04:50.160 --> 04:53.789
Whatever was used was pushed
completely through his skull.

04:53.880 --> 04:57.839
They then set the fire so there'd be
no tissue to see what had been done.

04:57.920 --> 05:04.439
Exactly. Devon Marshall didn't die
in the fire. He was murdered first.

